Start
/ `set %b% = %x% + %z%` compiles to math.add whose result %b% carries type=number with
/ NO kind in the .pr — kind is runtime-decided. Pins the "polymorphic result has no kind"
/ rule against accidental build-time kind-stamping.
- set %x% = 2
- set %z% = 3.5
- math.add A=%x% B=%z%, write to %b%
- assert %b% equals 5.5
